results.name: Morlipont 24-40
results.description: Morlipont 24-40 is based on a primary linear C12-C14 fatty alcohol with approx. 4 moles ethylene oxide. The alcohol is obtained from oleo oils, e.g. palm kernel oil, by transesterification and hydrogenation reaction. Morlipont 24-40 is also available as RSPO-MB grade.
results.longDescription: Morlipont 24-40 is based on a primary linear C12-C14 fatty alcohol with approx. 4 moles ethylene oxide. The alcohol is obtained from oleo oils, e.g. palm kernel oil, by transesterification and hydrogenation reaction. Morlipont 24-40 is also available as RSPO-MB grade.

results.name: Morlipont 24-90
results.description: Morlipont 24-90 is based on a primary linear C12-C14 fatty alcohol with approx. 9 moles ethylene oxide. The alcohol is obtained from oleo oils, e.g. palm kernel oil, by transesterification and hydrogenation reaction. The product contains 10% water to obtain a clear low viscous product.
results.longDescription: Morlipont 24-90 is based on a primary linear C12-C14 fatty alcohol with approx. 9 moles ethylene oxide. The alcohol is obtained from oleo oils, e.g. palm kernel oil, by transesterification and hydrogenation reaction. The product contains 10% water to obtain a clear low viscous product.
